A set is a n unordered collection of unique elements. 
Sets are used to store multiple items in a single variable
It is a built in data type used to eliminate duplicate values
and perform highly efficient membership test.

A set is a collection of unordered, unchangeable and unindexed data type.
it is return in curly bracket.

Example :
thisset = {"apple", "banana", "cherry"}
print(thisset)


